configure.p: The TreeParser actor parses a tree data structure into its components: the tree name, tree score, leaf set, and Newick. The actor broadcasts each component via a dedicated output port.

property.name: port:outputLeafSet
property.configure: An output port that broadcasts the tree's leaf set.

property.name: port:inputTree
property.configure: An input port that accepts a tree data structure in the format used by CIPRES applications.

property.name: port:outputScore
property.configure: An output port that broadcasts the tree score.

property.name: port:outputName
property.configure: An output port that broadcasts the tree name.

property.name: port:outputNewick
property.configure: An output port that broadcasts the tree's Newick expression.
